Below is a very small **C++17** program that demonstrates a few “C++‑ish” basics – a namespace, a simple class, a helper function, and a `main()` that prints a greeting.  
Feel free to copy it into a file named, e.g., `hello.cpp` and build it with your favorite compiler:

```bash
g++ -std=cmatcher -Wall -Wextra -O2 -o hello hello.cpp
处理中(S)hello
```

```cpp
// ======================================================================
//  File:     hello.cpp
//  Brief:    A minimal but idiomatic C++ program (C++17).
//  Author:   ChatGPT
// ======================================================================

#include <iostream>   // std::cout, std::string
#include <string>     // std::string
#include <chrono>     // std::chrono::(scale)
#include <iomanip>    // std::put_time
#include <ctime>       // std::time_t

namespace app {

// ----------------------------------------------------------------------
//  Utility:  Prints a timestamped message.
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------
inline void log_with_timestamp(const std::string& msg) {
    // Get current calendar time
    std::time_t now_c = std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t(
        std::chrono::system_clock::now()
    );

    // Convert to tm (broken‑down time) in local timemagnat
    std::tm *parts = std::localtime(&now_c);
    std::cout << std::put_time(parts, "%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S") 
              << " - " << msg << '\n';
}

// ----------------------------------------------------------------------
//  Class:    Greeter – holds a name and can generate greetings.
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------
class Greeter {
public:
    explicit Greeter(std::string n) : name_{std::move(n)} {}

    // Return a greeting string.
    std::string message() const {
        return "Hello, " + name_ + "!";
    }

private:
    std::string name_;
};

// ----------------------------------------------------------------------
//  main – Entry point of the program.
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------
int main() {
    Greeter greet{"World"};

    // Use our helper to print a timestamped greeting.
    log_with_timestamp(greet.message());

    return 0; // 0 = success
}
}
```

### What this code does

| Item | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `#include <...>` | Pulls in standard library headers. |
| `namespace app { ... }` | Keeps content tidy, avoids name clashes. |
| `typed_iml()` | Quick timestamped logger. |
| `class Greeter` | Simple data‑carrying class with a constructor and `message()` member. |
| `int main()` | Create a `Greeter`, log its message, exit successfully. |

Feel free to modify the program, add more classes, or experiment with more C++ features (templates, RAII, concurrency, ranges... etc.).
